The path to self love and acceptance is long and difficult. I genuinely believe tattoos act as a catalyst to a deeper connection to ourselves. 
The pain and healing that comes along from the process of tattooing is oddly paralleled to the journey we take to understanding who we are.
~
Have you every experienced that type of growth after a tattooed? I’d love to hear about it.
~
This is a cover up of self-harm scars and an old tattoo. I hope you enjoy.
Thank you Sara. 
#selflove #selfdiscovery #traditionaltattoo #coveruptattoo #tattooing #healing #selfharm #pittsburgh #nyc  #tattooartist

✨🪴3 years at @phippsconservatory 🌿✨
🤗😊🤗 and about 1 year anniversary of the Hawaii exhibit in our tropical forest room 🌺 ALL the while I was training for my Master gardener. It has been an absolute HONOR to be a part of this incredible organization, it’s history, and to have a hand in its show. An art experience every time I set foot in the building.
~
In the second photo, I hand planted everything you see… 👀 and the LAST photo you can see how MUCH that plot has grown. It shocks me to know that some of you are gaining joy and inspiration from the hard work of my hands and the geniuses I work with. That is magical.
~
I implore you go check out the masterful bonsai and orchid show now on display. And if you happen to catch me in the trees… Say hi! 🤗
~

🌲My first day working for the bonsai and Japanese garden of @phippsconservatory 😭🤯🤓
~
For nearly 12 years I’ve come to this garden to enjoy its beautiful bonsai collection….and now!? Somehow, I get to tend to these SAME trees that I saw before.
I can’t explain the joy I felt pruning this nearly 70 year old scotch pine today. 
~ It is an honor I do not take lightly. Please come out and see these natural masterpieces, you won’t be disappointed. 
You’ll see time and effort in a new worldly way.
~

5️⃣ years at @kyklopstattoo 👁️
~
June 1st 2018 I moved to Pittsburgh and that same day tattooed @lowdef_ in the greenroom of Stage AE at @themenzingers show…
My life has changed drastically since:
•Queerness has blessed me with freedom
•My clients trust me and challenge me to push this craft of tattooing
• I beat cancer…AGAIN
• I have real love in my life 🤖 
•The Kyklops family has grown
• I met a real life ghost, Casper

Please enjoy a wild selection of photos taken on June 1st over the years. Thank you for being in my life in whatever capacity. 
~
#kyklopstattoo #pittsburgh #pittsburghtattooer #5years #tattooing #pride

A much younger Jess wouldn’t believe this…Working with @phippsconservatory Bonsai, I’ve been designing, shaping, and tending to this Chinese Elm for the last few weeks. It is incredibly humbling to work with something living, and making decisions that affect the story being told.
•
Honestly, I am fascinated by tattooing for its longevity in craftsmanship, but bonsai is like working for the future in every step while also being present. It’s a communication for other generations, little movements to express a moment…to be interpreted by others. I love it.
I am grateful for this opportunity.
•
Please, visit Phipps Conservatory and do not miss the Japanese Garden. In it, you’ll see some INCREDIBLE bonsai that will knock you out. You’ll also see this elm on display, which I’ve given many hours toward searching for its story. I wonder what you’ll see in it…
•
Plus, the @theebillyporter show is amazing and expresses queerness and design in a brilliant way.
•
Thank you, I look forward to sharing more of this long work!

🗣️Finally get to share that I was selected for the Allegheny National Forest Centennial Artist Residency and will be showing my work at Crary Art Gallery this September!
It is my literal job to go out into PA’s only National park and make art 🤯😭🤯
•
I can’t believe I get to do this, to explore such a vast space and connect to something well beyond my existence—or even 100 years of time!
•
My goal is to explore what it is to have community in nature, while also depending on it for solitude and replenishment. Can we honor our natural environment and supplicate our needs?
I will be questioning that with my camera, brushes, and with my own two feet as I meander.
•
🫶But it is here that I request your help!!🫶
I’ll be taking most of the month of September off to do this and will be taking a major cut in my finances. Would you be able to show your support by donating? I am asking for money, but also 
* Physical Photos in Allegheny, 
* maps, brochures and advertisements of ANF
* Written stories of time you’ve spent there or your families history there.
I believe these ingredients will make for a proper show of the history of this great space.
•

❔⁉️Can you kill god with just a QUESTION? ⁉️❔
•
We cannot know peace before we know liberation. Freeing ourselves from cultural conditions and horrible self communication is essential to learning to love ourselves, our neighbors, and those we do not understand.
No god will ever help you solve a problem, nor assist you in communicating your needs. In fact, much of organized religion steals your ability to communicate with yourself. The idea of god (white jesus especially) convinces you to see the world as not being able to understand what you need….
•
Funny thing is that’s what you need the most: community, love, diversity, disagreement and nuance. It’s there you find god, amongst the voices of all people reaching outwardly.
•
I hope to erase god from my life, so only symbols and color remain. I do not  need any god, I only need you.
•

Meet #strangeoperator, Jess Scutella, tattooist and artist from America.
•
Jess got introduced to tattooing while pursuing their studies and developed keen interest in the aesthetics of classic American tattooing of the 1920-40s. They further explored influences of Japanese work, from woodblock paintings to contemporary anime motifs. Jess believes that augmenting our skin with designs, be it classic or contemporary, requires precision and knowledge about this ancient art form. They remain unwavering in their pursuit of knowing more about this art form and constantly honing their craft.
Catch Jess Scutella at Kula 2024. To pre-book your appointments with Jess Scutella, simply send him a direct message on Instagram @mrscutella or email them at mrscutellatattoos@gmail.com

For the last two years I’ve been studying ceramics at @firebornpottery in Pittsburgh’s Southside. It has been incredibly challenging to deeply learn about form, technique, and patience. Since I’ve never before worked in this medium, I’ve fallen deeply in love with the effort it takes to make such craft. 
More than that, I’ve found an incredible community in it all. Look at these beautiful people photographed!
•
Over the next few weeks I will FINALLY be sharing some of the pieces I’ve thrown, glazed, painted and formed. This is just a teaser of some brief moments in Fireborn and my home studio. So be sure to follow @strange_operators and keep an 👁️ on my webstore. I’d sure appreciate your sharing of this post. 
•
It’d make me so happy to eventually see humans using ceramics that I personally made 🥰😙

Tandem, collaborative back piece with my Co-conspirator and dear friend @davidj.montoya at @kyklopstattoo 🙂🙃🙂🙃🙂
•
Neither David nor I have coworked a project like this, so when we proposed it to Jared of @churchillpictures we were ecstatic to have a chance. In less than 3 months and 4 appointments, we knocked out his upper back piece. It is a melding of loud, bold traditional work with smooth black and gray realism.
•
This is not a project for the weak of heart…it’s EXTREMELY challenging, but incredibly rewarding. David and I would be interested in doing more conceptual and collaborative pieces like this. So if you’re brave. Reach out: mrscutellatattoos@gmail.com or davidjmontoyatattoo@gmail.com
•
Thanks forever to Jared and his strength.
